    "question": "15.14 (a) Show that in general a boost in the spatial direction $\\mathbf{e}_{\\hat{\\mathbf{j}}}$ leaves invariant the physical components of the Riemann tensor $\\mathbb{R}_{\\hat{\\mathbf{t}}\\hat{\\mathbf{j}}\\hat{\\mathbf{t}}\\hat{\\mathbf{j}}}$ which are \"parallel\" to the boost. This is analogous to the invariance of $\\mathbf{E}_{\\hat{\\mathbf{j}}}$ and $\\mathbf{B}_{\\hat{\\mathbf{j}}}$ for a boost in the $\\mathbf{e}_{\\hat{\\mathbf{j}}}$ direction.",
